The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | 32 colleges for IFA tourney
                                                                                                                       7                                      32 colleges for IFA tourney
            A STAFF REPORTER                      
	Calcutta: Thirty-two colleges will take part in the Elliot Challenge Shield football tournament organised by the Indian Football Association (IFA) which will start from Tuesday.         
	The IFA has roped in Coca-Cola, who will be the title sponsors for this edition. The matches will be played on a knock-out basis at four venues  Mohammedan Sporting ground, Barasat Stadium, Khardah Stadium and Makardah Stadium.         
	The prize money this time has been increased considerably.         
	The winners will be getting Rs 75,000, while the runners-up will be richer by Rs 50,000.         
	The losing semi-finalists will be getting Rs 10,000 each, said IFA general secretary Utpal Ganguli.         
	It has been also learnt that best player of each match will be receiving a cash award of Rs 1,000 while the highest scorer, player-of-the-tournament and fair play trophy winners will be getting Rs 5,000 each.         
	Meanwhile, the IFA is planning to organise the final of the tournament at the Mohun Bagan ground.                                                                                                                     
